on 100mm, displaying wet season. information left top includes name, altitude coordinate location. right top values annual mean temperature mean precipitation.","code":"data(\"plotdata\") loc <- subset(plotdata,No==2) clim_plot(loc)"},{"path":"/articles/climplot_Intro.html","id":"solution-to-drawing-for-serveral-location","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"Climatic diagram drawing","what":"Solution to drawing for serveral location","title":"Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"clim_plotonly supports drawing diagrams one location time, recommend checking plot individually, importing multiple vectors climate data increases risk errors. Therefore, require automated plotting several locations, utilizing loop recommended:","code":"data(\"plotdata\") list <- unique(plotdata$No) par(mfrow=c(1,1)) for (i in 1:5){  k <- list[i] sub <- subset(plotdata,No==k) clim_plot(data=sub,ylabel = TRUE,           ylab1=\"Temperature(\\U{00B0}C)\",           ylab2=\"Precipitation(mm)\",            p50line = TRUE) }"},{"path":[]},{"path":"/articles/climplot_Intro.html","id":"plotting-the-frosty-months","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"Climatic diagram drawing > Other tips of climatic diagram plotting","what":"Plotting the frosty months","title":"Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"blocks light blue color x-axis represent months potential frost, dark blue ones confirmed frost.","code":"data(\"plotdata_Frost\") loc <- subset(plotdata_Frost,No==3) clim_plot(data=loc,ShowFrost = T)"},{"path":"/articles/climplot_Intro.html","id":"color-and-axis-modification","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"Climatic diagram drawing > Other tips of climatic diagram plotting","what":"Color and axis modification","title":"Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"color axis labels customized meet specific requirements. possible adjust colors line temperature precipitation, well patches humidity, aridity, 