hat":"References","title":"Obtain climate data for climatic diagram construction — clim_extract","text":"Guijarro J (2023). climatol: Climate Tools (Series Homogenization Derived Products), 4.0.0., https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=climatol.Fick, S.E. R.J. Hijmans, (2017). WorldClim 2: new 1km spatial resolution climate surfaces global land areas. International Journal Climatology 37 (12): 4302-4315.Harris, ., Osborn, T.J., Jones, P.D., Lister, D.H. (2020). Version 4 CRU TS monthly high-resolution gridded multivariate climate dataset. Scientific Data 7: 109.Walter H & Lieth H (1960): Klimadiagramm Weltatlas. G. Fischer, Jena.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/climate_data.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Obtain climate data for climatic diagram construction — clim_extract","text":"","code":"{ #import data of stations data(\"locdata\") #or create a new data.frame #Please modify the path of yours a <- \"D:/climplot/climdata/mean_mintemp\" b <- \"D:/climplot/climdata/mean_maxtemp\" c <- \"D:/climplot/climdata/mean_prec\" d <- \"D:/climplot/climdata/min_mintemp\" #extraction of climate data if (FALSE) { #not sure whether the folders are ready cli <- clim_extract(m,a,b,c) #calculate for forst months display cli <- clim_extract(m,a,b,c,Frost=T,d) } }"},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"clim_plot plots Walter & Lieth climatic diagram climate data different locations. based method function diagwl()package climatol, offers additional parameters color selection, axis labeling, location information display meet diverse research publishing needs.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"","code":"clim_plot(data,mlab=\"\",pcol=\"blue\",tcol=\"red\",wcol=\"green\",dcol=\"orange\", pfcol=\"#79e6e8\",sfcol=\"#09a0d1\",ylabel=FALSE,ylab1=NA,ylab2=NA,xlab=\"Month\", ShowFrost=FALSE,shem=FALSE,p3line=FALSE,p50line=FALSE,extremeT=FALSE, margen=c(4,4,5,4),per=NA)"},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"data data.frame(see details dataset plotdata) following 18 columns: : Serial number locations. location: Abbreviation locations. lon: Longitude locations decimal digit     (negative numbers indicating west longitude). lat: Latitude locations decimal digit     (negative numbers indicating south latitude). altitude: Altitude locations. type: labels climate data, encompassing annual average precipitation,     annual average minimum temperature annual average maximum temperature.     event Frost=True, also incorporate annual extreme minimum temperature. 1-12: column names particular climate data type     correspond monthly values ranging January December. columns containing information may placed aforementioned columns,     disregarded subsequent processes. mlab vector 12 monthly labels X axis.Deafult numeric. Alternatively, set 'en' 'es' can specified display month names English Spanish respectively. (original parameter referenced function diagwl()). pcol Color precipitation curve. Default \"blue\". tcol Color temperature curve. Default \"red\". wcol Color humid season polygon. Default \"green\". dcol Color arid season polygon. Default \"orange\". pfcol Color potential frosty months. Default \"#79e6e8\". use ShowFrost= FALSE. sfcol Color confirmed frosty months. Default \"#09a0d1\". use ShowFrost= FALSE. ylabel logical value whether using customized label y axis. Default FALSE. ylab1 character value label y axis temperature. Default NA. ylab2 character value label y axis precipitation. Default NA. xlab character value label x axis. Default \"Month\". ShowFrost logical value whether marking forst months. Default FALSE. shem logical value whether keeping summer period central zone graphic (diagram begin plot July data). Default FALSE. Useful location southern hemisphere (original parameter referenced function diagwl()). p3line logical value whether displaying supplementary precipitation line referenced three times temperature. Default FALSE (original parameter referenced function diagwl()). p50line logical value whether displaying supplementary precipitation line 50°C-100mm. Default FALSE. extremeT logical value whether displaying extreme temperature. Default FALSE. margen vector control range plot. Default \"c(4,4,5,4)\" per parameter referenced function diagwl(). use temporarily. #'@details function extracts precipitation temperature arranged Worldclim Historical monthly weather data(https://worldclim.org/data/monthlywth.html) arranges data.frame constructing climatic diagram.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram provided locations, including annual variation temperature precipitation , well time humid arid season.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":"references","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"References","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"Guijarro J (2023). climatol: Climate Tools (Series Homogenization Derived Products), 4.0.0., https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=climatol.Walter H & Lieth H (1960): Klimadiagramm Weltatlas. G. Fischer, Jena.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/climatic_diagram.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram construction — clim_plot","text":"","code":"{ data(\"plotdata\") test <- subset(plotdata,No==10) clim_plot(data=test,ylabel = TRUE,         ylab1=\"Temperature(\\U{00B0}C)\",         ylab2=\"Precipitation(mm)\",         p50line = TRUE)  #use loop to plot multiple diagrams simultaneously list <- unique(plotdata$No) par(mfrow=c(1,1)) for (i in 1:5){  k <- list[i] sub <- subset(plotdata,No==k) clim_plot(data=sub,ylabel = TRUE,           ylab1=\"Temperature(\\U{00B0}C)\",           ylab2=\"Precipitation(mm)\",            p50line = TRUE) }  }"},{"path":"/reference/locdata.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"An example of data format for ","title":"An example of data format for ","text":"dataset containing abbreviation, coordinates altitude different locations.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/locdata.html","id":"format","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Format","title":"An example of data format for ","text":"data frame 10 rows 6 variables: Serial number locations location Abbreviation locations lon Longitude locations decimal digit lat Latitude locations decimal digit altitude Altitude locations name Full name locations","code":""},{"path":"/reference/locdata.html","id":"source","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Source","title":"An example of data format for ","text":"NULL","code":""},{"path":"/reference/locdata.html","id":"details","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Details","title":"An example of data format for ","text":"5 columns dataset: \"\", \"location\", \"lon\", \"lat\", \"altitude\" essential diagram construction, columns \"name\" just remark.","code":""},{"path":"/reference/plotdata.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"An example of data.frame export from ","title":"An example of data.frame export from ","text":"dataset exported function clim_extract forclimatic diagrams construction without frosty months display. contains abbreviation, coordinates altitude different locations, well values 3 types climate data.","code":