ng annual extreme minimum temperatures. mode, data.frame exported includes 5 kinds information locations(data.frame imported), values 4 kinds climate factors among 12 months. annual extreme minimum temperature included new row every location. data.frame mode stores data plotdata_Frost package, example function export. Hereto clim_extact obtained essential information Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing.","code":"#Modify the path of yours a <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmin\" b <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmax\" c <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/prec\"  #extraction of climate data plotdata <- clim_extract(locdata, a, b, c) #Modify the path of yours a <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmin\" b <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmax\" c <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/prec\" d <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/extmin\" #extraction of climate data  plotdata <- clim_extract(locdata,a,b,c,Frost = TRUE,d) }"},{"path":"/articles/climplot_Intro.html","id":"climatic-diagram-drawing","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"","what":"Climatic diagram drawing","title":"Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"function clim_plot can draw Walter & Lieth climatic diagram plotting different styles color scheme information presentation. refers function diagwl()CRAN package climatol.","code":""},{"path":"/articles/climplot_Intro.html","id":"walter-lieth-climatic-diagram-drawing-of-a-single-location","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"Climatic diagram drawing","what":"Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing of a single location","title":"Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"Take data plotdata plotdata_Frost example, import clim_plot.  figure : red curve represents annual variation temperature, blue one represents precipitation variation. two curves form two kinds patches indicating humidity aridity levels. line-filled patches represent humid seasons scattered points represent arid seasons. polygon filled color precipitation curve indicates months precipitati