2: new 1km spatial resolution climate surfaces global land areas. International Journal Climatology 37 (12): 4302-4315. Harris, ., Osborn, T.J., Jones, P.D., Lister, D.H. (2020). Version 4 CRU TS monthly high-resolution gridded multivariate climate dataset. Scientific Data 7: 109.","code":""},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"安装与加载","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"","what":"安装与加载","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"从gitee和github 安装最新的开发版本，请安装R包remotes和git2r。 如果需要查看更多帮助信息，请在后面加上代码build_vignettes= TRUE。","code":"install.packages('remotes')  #from github remotes::install_github(\"auman-chan/climplot\") #from gitee install.packages('git2r') remotes::install_git(\"https://gitee.com/auman-chan/climplot.git\")  #add vignettes remotes::install_github(\"auman-chan/climplot\",build_vignettes= TRUE)  remotes::install_git(\"https://gitee.com/auman-chan/climplot.git\",                      build_vignettes= TRUE)"},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"使用前数据准备","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"","what":"使用前数据准备","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"Worldclim气候数据是本软件包必不可少的，由于其全球尺度栅格数据的文件较大，软件包中无法容纳需要的气候数据。因此，请在使用前从Figshare获取对应的气候数据集。 此数据集包括4个文件夹，共48个tif文件，其中包括年均最低气温、年均最高气温、年均降水和年极端最低气温。","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"气候数据提取","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"使用示例","what":"气候数据提取","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"使用前需要按格式整理好绘图地点的信息。这个包中的数据 locdata 是 导入数据格式的样例。导入的数据框必须包含5列，顺序如下: :目标地点的序号 location:目标地点的缩写 lon:目标地点的经度，以十进制表示，负数表示西经 lat:目标地点的纬度，以十进制表示，负数表示南纬 altitude:目标地点的高度 上述列的后面允许添加其他包含信息的列，但在后续处理中将被舍弃。 在准备好气候数据集和地点信息后，向函数 clim_extract 导入三个气候数据集的数据框和数据集路径： 导出带有气候数据的数据框,其包含5种地点信息(与导入数据框中的相同)，以及12个月份的3种气候数值。 导出数据框架存储在此包的数据plotdata中，作为函数导出结果的示例。","code":"#Example data in this package data(\"locdata\") #Modify the path of yours a <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmin\" b <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmax\" c <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/prec\"  #extraction of climate data  plotdata <- clim_extract(locdata,a,b,c)"},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"walter-lieth的气候图绘制","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"使用示例","what":"Walter & Lieth的气候图绘制","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"以plotdata数据为例，导入到函数clim_plot中：  在上图中: 红色曲线代表气温的年际变化，蓝色曲线代表降水的年际变化。这两条曲线闭合形成了两种斑块，表示湿度和干燥程度。竖线填充的斑块代表湿润季节，散点填充的斑块代表干旱季节。与降水曲线颜色相同的多边形表示降水量大于100mm的月份，表示雨季。 左上角的信息包括名称、海拔高度和位置坐标。右上方为年平均气温和年平均降水量。","code":"data(\"plotdata\") loc <- subset(plotdata,No==2) clim_plot(loc)"},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"其他参考","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"","what":"其他参考","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"更多参考内容请阅读软件包内的帮助文件，以及vignettes中的信息。","code":""},{"path":"/articles/README.zh-CN.html","id":"参考文献","dir":"Articles","previous_headings":"","what":"参考文献","title":"climplot：用于绘制 Walter & Lieth 气候图的流程化工具","text":"Guijarro J (2023). climatol: Climate Tools (Series Homogenization Derived Products), 4.0.0., https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=climatol. Fick, S.E. R.J. Hijmans, (2017). WorldClim 2: new 1km spatial resolution climate surfaces global land areas. International Journal Climatology 37 (12): 4302-4315. Harris, ., Osborn, T.J., Jones, P.D., Lister, D.H. (2020). Version 4 CRU TS monthly high-resolution gridded multivariate climate dataset. Scientific Data 7: 109. Walter H & Lieth H (1960): Klimadiagramm Weltatlas. G. Fischer, Jena.","code":""},{"path":"/authors.html","id":null,"dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Authors","title":"Authors and Citation","text":"Auman Chan. Maintainer.","code":""},{"path":"/authors.html","id":"citation","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Citation","title":"Authors and Citation","text":"Chan (2023). climplot: climplot: Facilitate tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing. R package version 0.2.1, https://github.com/auman-chan/climplot.","code":"@Manual{,   title = {climplot: climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing},   author = {Auman Chan},   year = {2023},   note = {R package version 0.2.1},   url = {https://github.com/auman-chan/climplot}, }"},{"path":"/index.html","id":"climplot-facilitate-and-tailor-walter--lieth-climatic-diagram-drawing","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"climplot aims collect crucial climate data global locations render Walter & Lieth climatic diagrams user-friendly personalized manner. main features package : use worldwide climate data obtain standardized reliable data drawing Walter & Lieth climatic diagrams provision parameter customize plots display comprehensive information package offers functions : Obtain climate data draw Walter & Lieth Climatic Diagram global locations Draw Walter & Lieth climatic diagram Revise color scheme information presentation diagram","code":""},{"path":"/index.html","id":"installing-and-loading","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Installing and loading","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"install latest developmental version github gitee, need R packages remotes git2r. want install vignettes package, please add build_vignettes= TRUE.","code":"install.packages('remotes')  #from github remotes::install_github(\"auman-chan/climplot\") #from gitee install.packages('git2r') remotes::install_git(\"https://gitee.com/auman-chan/climplot.git\")  #add vignettes remotes::install_github(\"auman-chan/climplot\",build_vignettes= TRUE)  remotes::install_git(\"https://gitee.com/auman-chan/climplot.git\",                      build_vignettes= TRUE)"},{"path":"/index.html","id":"data-preparation","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Data preparation","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"climate data provided Worldclim indispensable, however, due global-scale raster layer format, file size substantial accommodated within package. Therefore, kindly obtain climate dataset Figshare use. dataset comprises four folders total 48 .tif files, include annual average minimum temperature, annual average maximum temperature, annual average precipitation, annual extreme minimum temperature.","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"/index.html","id":"extraction-of-climate-data","dir":"","previous_headings":"Eaxmple","what":"Extraction of climate data","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"Information target locations ready extraction. data locdata package can example import data.frame. must contain five columns following order: : Serial number locations location: Abbreviation locations lon: Longitude locations decimal digit (negative numbers indicating west longitude) lat: Latitude locations decimal digit (negative numbers indicating south latitude) altitude: Altitude locations extra columns information allowed behind columns , discarded following process. preparing climate dataset location information, import data.frame path three climate datasets function clim_extract: exported data.frame includes 5 kinds information locations(data.frame imported), values 3 kinds climate factors across 12 months. data.frame stores data plotdata package, example function export.","code":"#Example data in this package data(\"locdata\") #Modify the path of yours a <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmin\" b <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/tmax\" c <- \"G:/climplot/climdata/prec\"  #extraction of climate data  plotdata <- clim_extract(locdata, a, b, c)"},{"path":"/index.html","id":"climatic-diagram-drawing","dir":"","previous_headings":"Eaxmple","what":"Climatic diagram drawing","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"Take data plotdata plotdata_Frost example, import function clim_plot:  figure : red curve represents annual variation temperature, blue one represents precipitation variation. two curves form two types patches indicating humidity aridity levels. string-filled patches represent humid seasons scattered points represent arid seasons. polygon filled color precipitation curve indicates months precipitation 100mm, displaying wet season. information left top includes name, altitude coordinates locations. right top values annual mean temperature mean precipitation.","code":"data(\"plotdata\") loc <- subset(plotdata,No==2) clim_plot(loc)"},{"path":"/index.html","id":"more-inforamtion","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"More inforamtion","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"examples information, please view help pages websites package .","code":""},{"path":"/index.html","id":"reference","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Reference","title":"climplot: Facilitate and tailor Walter & Lieth climatic diagram drawing","text":"Guijarro J (2023). climatol: Climate Tools (Series Homogenization Derived Products), 4.0.0., https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=climatol. Fick, S.E. R.J. Hijmans, (2017). WorldClim 2: new 1km spatial resolution climate surfaces global land areas. International Journal Climatology 37 (12): 4302-4315. Harris, ., Osborn, T.J., Jones, P.D., Lister, D.H. (2020). Version 4 CRU TS monthly high-resolution gridded multivariate climate dataset. Scientific Data 7: 109. Walter H & Lieth H (1960): Klimadiagramm Weltatlas. G. Fischer, Jena.","code":""},{"path":"/LICENSE.html","id":null,"dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"GNU General Public License","title":"GNU General Public License","text":"Version 3, 29 June 2007Copyright © 2007 Free Software Foundation, Inc. <http://fsf.org/> Everyone permitted copy distribute verbatim copies license document, changing allowed.","code":""},{"path":"/LICENSE.html","id":"preamble","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Preamble","title":"GNU General Public License","text":"GNU General Public License free, copyleft license software kinds works. lic